description: Returns a list of PackageVersionSummary objects for package versions in a repository that match the request parameters. Package versions of all statuses will be returned by default when calling list-package-versions with no --status parameter.

parameters.name: domain
parameters.description: The name of the domain that contains the repository that contains the requested package versions.

parameters.name: repository
parameters.description: The name of the repository that contains the requested package versions.

parameters.name: format
parameters.description: The format of the package versions you want to list.

parameters.name: namespace
parameters.description: The namespace of the package that contains the requested package versions. The package component that specifies its namespace depends on its type. For example: The namespace of a Maven package version is its groupId. The namespace of an npm or Swift package version is its scope. The namespace of a generic package is its namespace. Python, NuGet, Ruby, and Cargo package versions do not contain a corresponding component, package versions of those formats do not have a namespace.

parameters.name: package
parameters.description: The name of the package for which you want to request package versions.

nested_items.name: defaultDisplayVersion
nested_items.description: The default package version to display. This depends on the package format:
For Maven and PyPI packages, it's the most recently published package version.
For npm packages, it's the version referenced by the latest tag. If the latest tag is not set, it's the most recently published package version.

nested_items.name: namespace
nested_items.description: The namespace of the package that contains the requested package versions. The package component that specifies its namespace depends on its type. For example:
The namespace of a Maven package version is its groupId.
The namespace of an npm or Swift package version is its scope.
The namespace of a generic package is its namespace.
Python, NuGet, Ruby, and Cargo package versions do not contain a corresponding component, package versions of those formats do not have a namespace.

nested_items.name: versions
nested_items.description: The returned list of PackageVersionSummary objects.

nested_items.name: revision
nested_items.description: The revision associated with a package version.

nested_items.name: status
nested_items.description: A string that contains the status of the package version. It can be one of the following:

nested_items.name: domainEntryPoint
nested_items.description: A DomainEntryPoint object that contains information about from which repository or external connection the package version was added to the domain.

nested_items.name: repositoryName
nested_items.description: The name of the repository that a package was originally published to.

nested_items.name: externalConnectionName
nested_items.description: The name of the external connection that a package was ingested from.

nested_items.name: originType
nested_items.description: Describes how the package version was originally added to the domain. An INTERNAL origin type means the package version was published directly to a repository in the domain. An EXTERNAL origin type means the package version was ingested from an external connection.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: If there are additional results, this is the token for the next set of results.
